{
  "stem": "5356.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And after they-- it was the-- under-- the name was Rabbi [?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Scheuer ?] Heschel [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Memezebesch ?].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And after they-- the thing stopped-- I remember when I used to go there with my father on Saturday afternoons in the summer to learn [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As young kids, we used to climb up on the step ladder and to look in to see-- that-- it was called a [INAUDIBLE], but actually, it was a piece of steel.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was about four inches wide, which his name was engraved in it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And if they were-- people came to visit the city.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They old-- the oldest used to bring down to show it-- what it is.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was still there when I was there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, we used to go up and see it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And all of that came at the end, you know, in 1942.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember that Friday morning-- I think it was September the 3rd-- we heard on the radio that the Germans invaded Poland.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we heard on the radio, nadchodzi, nadchodzi-- that the planes are coming, you know, closer by.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And three days later, they bombed-- a few bombs fell on our hometown because you could see people streaming east.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, from the west of the country, streaming east, towards the side of the Vistula.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you saw the units of the army, you know, in disarray, going back.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then you saw-- in Tuesday-- Thursday, the next-- Friday started the war and Thursday afternoon, the first Germans arrived in the city.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The same night, half of the city, the main part of the city, was burned down.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They claimed that somebody, that one of the Poles fired a shot and that gave them the excuse to burn down part of the city.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
